# widget — design conventions

The widget UI is built from Figma frames in the "🧠 Application" file. Keep it
consistent and themeable as more states land.

## Conventions

- **Use theme tokens, not hardcoded hex.** Colors/radii/spacing are mapped from
  Figma into `src/index.css` as `--max-*` variables and exposed as utilities
  (`bg-max-surface`, `text-max-text-80`, `border-max-card-border`,
  `text-max-link`, `rounded-bubble`, `rounded-card`, `rounded-icon`, …). Add a
  new token there when the design needs one; don't scatter `#hex` in components.
- **Components live under `src/components/`** (one concern per file); shared
  shadcn primitives stay in `src/components/ui/`. Add shadcn components through
  the established New York / `components.json` setup.
- **Icons come from `lucide-react`**, not exported Figma SVGs. The only bundled
  asset is the Max mascot (`src/assets/max-avatar.svg`).
- **Mark UI not present in Figma** with a `// DERIVED: not in Figma — review`
  comment (empty/error/refusal states, the sources collapsible, score/preview,
  feedback thumbs behavior, keyboard handling, page-level layout). This flags
  exactly what a designer still needs to sign off on.
- **No typewriter / streaming in render.** Answers display in full immediately
  (the typewriter effect is a separate step). Render answers as plain text with
  preserved line breaks; introducing a markdown renderer is a flagged change.

## Why

A real, unique design now exists. Funnelling colors/spacing through tokens keeps
it themeable, and the `DERIVED` marker keeps the line between "matches Figma" and
"our best guess" reviewable instead of invisible.
